[{"content":"To see what a **translation** is, please grab the point and move it around.\n\n[[☃ interaction 1]]\n\nNice! You *translated* the point. In geometry, a translation moves a thing up and down or left and right.\n\nHere, try translating this line:\n\n[[☃ interaction 2]]\n\nNotice how the line's disposition remained the same as you moved it. Translations only move things from one place to another; they don't change their arrangement or direction.\n\nNow that we've got a basic understanding of what translations are, let's learn how to use them on the coordinate plane.","images":{},"widgets":{"interaction 1":{"type":"interaction","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"static":false,"graph":{"editableSettings":["canvas","graph"],"box":[260,120],"labels":["x","y"],"range":[[-5,5],[-5,5]],"gridStep":[0.5,2],"markings":"none","snapStep":[1,1],"valid":true,"backgroundImage":{"url":null,"width":0,"height":0},"showProtractor":false,"showRuler":false,"rulerLabel":"","rulerTicks":10,"tickStep":[1,2]},"elements":[{"type":"movable-point","key":"movable-point-96a605","options":{"startX":"0","startY":"0","constraint":"none","snap":0.5,"constraintFn":"0","constraintXMin":"-5","constraintXMax":"5","constraintYMin":"-5","constraintYMax":"5","varSubscript":0}}]},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}},"interaction 2":{"type":"interaction","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"static":false,"graph":{"editableSettings":["canvas","graph"],"box":[260,120],"labels":["x","y"],"range":[[-10,10],[-10,10]],"gridStep":[1,1],"markings":"none","snapStep":[1,1],"valid":true,"backgroundImage":{"url":null,"width":0,"height":0},"showProtractor":false,"showRuler":false,"rulerLabel":"","rulerTicks":10,"tickStep":[1,1]},"elements":[{"type":"movable-line","key":"movable-line-16b1da","options":{"startX":"-5","startY":"-3","endX":"5","endY":"5","constraint":"none","snap":0.5,"constraintFn":"0","constraintXMin":"-10","constraintXMax":"0","constraintYMin":"-10","constraintYMax":"2","startSubscript":0,"endSubscript":1}}]},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}}}},{"content":"# Translations on the coordinate plane\n\nCoordinates allow us to be very precise about the translations we perform.\n\nWithout coordinates, we could say something like, \"We get $\\maroonD{B'}$ by translating $\\blueD{B}$ down and to the right.\"\n\n![](web+graphie://ka-perseus-graphie.s3.amazonaws.com/4cefbcb284fe4e9faa7bb67dc1c55f22534097f9)\n\nBut that's not very precise. If we use a coordinate grid, we can say something more exact: \"We get $\\maroonD{B'}$ by translating $\\blueD{B}$ by 5 units to the right and 4 units down.\"\n\n![](web+graphie://ka-perseus-graphie.s3.amazonaws.com/78f0c6ffa4f435bb27d80c75adbee450ed6d7a71)\n\nMore compactly, we can describe this as **a translation by $\\langle 5,-4 \\rangle$.**\n\nThe negative sign in front of the 4 tells us the vertical shift is downwards instead of upwards. Similarly, a translation to the left is indicated by the first value being negative.\n\n###Sources and images\n\nFor any transformation, we have the **source** figure, which is the figure we are performing the transformation upon, and the **image** figure, which is the result of the transformation. For example, in our translation, the source point was $\\blueD{B}$ and the image point was $\\maroonD{B'}$.\n\nNote that we indicated the image by $\\maroonD{B'}$, pronounced B prime. It is common, when working with transformations, to use the same letter for the image and the source, simply adding the \"prime\" suffix to the image.","images":{"web+graphie://ka-perseus-graphie.s3.amazonaws.com/4cefbcb284fe4e9faa7bb67dc1c55f22534097f9":{"width":255,"height":255},"web+graphie://ka-perseus-graphie.s3.amazonaws.com/78f0c6ffa4f435bb27d80c75adbee450ed6d7a71":{"width":281,"height":281}},"widgets":{}},{"content":"# Let's try some practice problems\n\n[[☃ explanation 1]]\n\n### Problem 1\n\n[[☃ graded-group 1]]\n\n[[☃ explanation 2]]","images":{},"widgets":{"explanation 1":{"type":"explanation","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"static":false,"showPrompt":"Click here to watch Sal solving an example problem, if you want.","hidePrompt":"Hide video.","explanation":"[[☃ video 1]]","widgets":{"video 1":{"options":{"static":false,"location":"translation-example"},"type":"video","version":{"major":0,"minor":0},"id":"video 1","graded":true,"alignment":"block","static":false}}},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}},"graded-group 1":{"type":"graded-group","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"content":"**Translate the line segment by $\\langle -8,3 \\rangle$.**\n\n[[☃ transformer 1]]\n\n","images":{},"widgets":{"transformer 1":{"type":"transformer","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"starting":{"shape":{"type":["lineSegment"],"coords":[[7,3],[3,-4]],"options":[{}]},"transformations":[]},"graphMode":"interactive","listMode":"dynamic","tools":{"translation":{"enabled":true,"required":false,"constraints":{}},"rotation":{"enabled":false,"required":false,"constraints":{"fixed":false},"coord":[1,6]},"reflection":{"enabled":false,"required":false,"constraints":{"fixed":false},"coords":[[2,-4],[2,2]]},"dilation":{"enabled":false,"required":false,"constraints":{"fixed":false},"coord":[6,6]}},"drawSolutionShape":false,"gradeEmpty":false,"graph":{"range":[[-10,10],[-10,10]],"step":[1,1],"markings":"grid","labels":["x","y"],"backgroundImage":{"url":"web+graphie://ka-perseus-graphie.s3.amazonaws.com/dfba975299754d2a8cc0600184bd7a9711bc175e","width":400,"height":400},"showProtractor":false,"showRuler":false,"rulerLabel":"","rulerTicks":10,"gridStep":[1,1],"snapStep":[0.5,0.5]},"version":1.2,"correct":{"transformations":[{"vector":[-8,3],"type":"translation"}],"shape":{"type":["lineSegment"],"coords":[[-1,6],[-5,-1]],"options":[{}]}}},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}}}},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}},"explanation 2":{"type":"explanation","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"static":false,"showPrompt":"I need help!","hidePrompt":"Got it, thanks!","explanation":"First, click on the Translate button. The segment's endpoints will light up.\n\nThen, drag one of the endpoints 8 units to the left and 3 units up.\n\nOnce you start moving the segment, a label will indicate the translation according to the current position of the segment.","widgets":{}},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}}}},{"content":"### Problem 2\n\n[[☃ graded-group 1]]\n\n[[☃ explanation 1]]","images":{},"widgets":{"graded-group 1":{"type":"graded-group","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"content":"**Translate the triangle by $\\langle 2,6 \\rangle$.**\n\n[[☃ transformer 1]]\n","images":{},"widgets":{"transformer 1":{"type":"transformer","alignment":"default","static":false,"graded":true,"options":{"starting":{"shape":{"type":["polygon-3"],"coords":[[-6,-3],[-6,2],[0,-3]],"options":[{}]},"transformations":[]},"graphMode":"interactive","listMode":"dynamic","tools":{"translation":{"enabled":true,"required":false,"constraints":{}},"rotation":{"enabled":false,"required":false,"constraints":{"fixed":false},"coord":[1,6]},"reflection":{"enabled":false,"required":false,"constraints":{"fixed":false},"coords":[[2,-4],[2,2]]},"dilation":{"enabled":false,"required":false,"constraints":{"fixed":false},"coord":[6,6]}},"drawSolutionShape":false,"gradeEmpty":false,"graph":{"range":[[-10,10],[-10,10]],"step":[1,1],"markings":"grid","labels":["x","y"],"backgroundImage":{"url":"web+graphie://ka-perseus-graphie.s3.amazonaws.com/55b92acc531b5da0b4729b2c9c8f192c4c1e11f6","width":400,"height":400},"showProtractor":false,"showRuler":false,"rulerLabel":"","rulerTicks":10,"gridStep":[1,1],"snapStep":[0.5,0.5]},"version":1.2,"correct":{"transformations":[{"vector":[2,6],"type":"translation"}],"shape":{"type":["polygon-3"],"coords":[[-4,3],[-4,8],[2,3]],"options":[{}]}}},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}}}},"version":{"major":0,"minor":0}},"explanati